Write two variable names that would be valid and well-named - discount_price original_price
Write two variable names that would be valid but not well-named - discountprice originalprice
Write two variable names that would not be valid - 1number 2number
What is the naming convention for variables in Python? - variable must be in lowercase with a under score in between the words
What is a constant? Give an example of when you would use one - Constant is a variable that cannot be changed. We use constant when we're sure of the value.
What is the naming convention for constants? - Constant must be in all caps.

